data.title: New on Netflix in August 2024 - Netflix Tudum
data.meta_description: Here are the movies, TV shows and original series that premiere on Netflix this month including The Umbrella Academy, Emily in Paris, A Good Girl's Guide to Murder, and more.
data.text:
New on Netflix in August 2024

Emily in Paris and The Umbrella Academy return, A Good Girl’s Guide to Murder is on the case, and more.

By Erin Corbett

Aug. 12, 2024

August is always a period of transition. As the end of summer approaches, the slowness of the month pairs with the looming responsibilities of fall. If you need a little something extra to get you through the “Sunday Scaries” of August, there are still plenty of streams left for you before the end of summer. Crack the case on a murder mystery in a small English town in A Good Girl’s Guide To Murder, or jet-set on a European escapade with Emily Cooper as she returns for Emily in Paris Season 4, Part 1.

Catch up with father-son duo Rob Lowe and John Owen Lowe in Unstable Season 2; if you’re looking for a different kind of family drama, don’t miss Jeff Goldblum as the charismatic yet cruel Zeus, king of the gods, in KAOS. And if an expedition between land and sea sounds exciting, you’ll want to grab your lasso because Sandy Cheeks and SpongeBob SquarePants are heading to Texas to save Bikini Bottom in Saving Bikini Bottom: The Sandy Cheeks Movie.

Here’s everything else you can hit play on in August.

August 1

The Umbrella Academy

Season 4

The Hargreeves siblings have scattered after the climactic showdown at the Hotel Oblivion led to a complete reset of their timeline. Stripped of their powers, each is left to fend for themselves and find a new normal — with wildly varying degrees of success. Yet the trappings of their uncanny new world prove too hard to ignore for very long. Their father, Reginald, alive and well, has stepped out of the shadows and into the public eye, overseeing a powerful and nefarious business empire. A mysterious association known as the Keepers holds clandestine meetings believing the reality they’re living in is a lie and a great reckoning is coming. As these strange new forces conspire around them, the Umbrella Academy must come together one last time — and risk upsetting the shaky peace they’ve all endured so much to secure — to finally set things right.
